## Rules

- All emails sent via queue (BullMQ) — never block HTTP
- `EmailService` is the only class that calls the email provider
- Always log email sends (success and failure) with recipient and template name
- Never log email body content — it may contain PII
- Always have retry logic on queue jobs (attempts: 3)
- Use typed template context objects — never pass untyped `any`
- Password reset links must expire (include expiry in template context)
- All links in emails use HTTPS
- Test email sending with a sandbox/test mode in development

---

## Environment Variables

```env
EMAIL_FROM=noreply@yourdomain.com
EMAIL_FROM_NAME=YourApp
RESEND_API_KEY=re_xxxx
# or
SENDGRID_API_KEY=SG.xxxx
```

---

## Forbidden

❌ Sending emails synchronously in HTTP handlers
❌ Hardcoded sender email address
❌ Logging email body content (PII risk)
❌ Missing retry on email queue jobs
❌ HTTP links in emails (must be HTTPS)
❌ Password reset links without expiry
❌ `any` type for template context
❌ Calling email provider SDK directly from services (use EmailService)
